"{\"uid\": \"newsus.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-04-Sprinter-Andre-De-Grasse-discusses-his-expectations-at-Paris-Olympics-1vMwz3MnpxS-p.html\", \"text\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use. You can change your cookie settings through your browser.  Dan Williams  Copied  Canadian sprint star Andre De Grasse advanced to the men's 100-meter semifinal at the Paris Olympics. At Tokyo 2020, he won gold in the men\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s 200 meters as well as a bronze in the 100 meters. After struggling with injuries over the last few years, he too believes he\\u00e2\\u0080\\u0099s back to his best and is confident he can add to his Olympic medal collection.  For more, check out our exclusive content onCGTN Nowand subscribe to our weekly newsletter,The China Report.  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466  SITEMAP  EXPLORE MORE  DOWNLOAD OUR APP  Copyright \\u00c2\\u00a9 2024 CGTN.\\u00e4\\u00ba\\u00acICP\\u00e5\\u00a4\\u008720000184\\u00e5\\u008f\\u00b7  Disinformation report hotline: 010-85061466\"}"